news.title: Ahmedabad civic body warns 147 societies to pay tax or face water and sewer disconnections
news.para: Notices were also issued to the chairmen of 147 societies in the South and East Zones, warning of imminent disconnection of water and sewer services if dues remain unpaid.

news.title: PMAY-Gramin to include self-survey option for next phase
news.para: In a written reply, Union Minister of State for Rural Development Chandra Sekhar Pemmasani said the government approved the proposal for implementation of the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana-Gramin (PMAY-G) for five more years.

news.title: Lucknow development body allocates homes to 369 applicants under PMAY
news.para: ​​The allotment included 209 houses under the Sharda Nagar Extension Scheme and 160 under Sector-N of Basant Kunj Yojana.

news.title: Kanpur development body plans urban expansion with high rises and modern facilities
news.para: Recently, about 20,588 hectares of land from 80 villages surrounding the Highway Defence Corridor and the Ring Road has been incorporated into its jurisdiction.

news.title: Lucknow development body demolishes five-storey complex in Indiranagar
news.para: The complex, spanning approximately 10,000 sqft, included shops and 10 flats. The complex, owned by builder Amar Agarwal, was constructed without obtaining necessary approvals and violated building regulations.

news.title: Karnataka CM questions Kerala govt's silence on offer to build 100 homes for landslide survivors
news.para: In a letter to CM Pinarayi Vijayan, he said that due to a lack of response from Kerala, Karnataka was not able to move forward with the commitment it made.

news.title: Bhubaneswar ADM issues show-cause notice to builder for not complying with ORERA order
news.para: According to sources, the builder executed a multi-storied housing project in Ghatikia but failed to deliver the houses on time. As a result, 18 aggrieved homebuyers approached ORERA, which asked the builder to pay a compensation of Rs 87.94 lakh.

news.title: YEIDA to offer hotel plots ahead of Noida airport launch
news.para: The scheme — scheduled for launch on Wednesday — encompasses 12 premium plots across sectors 28 and 29, specifically designed to accommodate high-end hospitality projects, including five-star hotels.

news.title: SC dismisses CBI plea against medical bail to DHFL's former director
news.para: A bench comprising Chief Justice Sanjiv Khanna and Justice Sanjay Kumar said the trial in the case was unlikely to conclude in 10 years and the amount involved was substantial.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body may amend bylaws to mandate solar panels for residential buildings
news.para: "Once implemented, approval of building maps will be subject to provision for solar panels. No completion certificate will be issued if the provisions are not made," a GDA official said.

news.title: Gurugram civic body uncovers six illegal colonies in Behrampur
news.para: Plots, sold at Rs 50,000-80,000 per square yard, have been carved out. Of the six patches inspected, three already had road networks and construction underway, while others were being levelled for development, officials said.

news.title: Over six lakh houses sanctioned under PMAY-U 2.0: Housing minister
news.para: Union housing and urban affairs minister Manohar Lal Khattar added that another one lakh houses will be sanctioned once the remaining seven states and UTs sign agreements with the housing ministry.

news.title: Maharashtra housing federation proposes single window clearance in new housing policy
news.para: The suggestion has come as the new govt prepares to finalise the policy, which was initially released in September this year but remained pending due to assembly elections and the model code of conduct.

news.title: CCI approves Blackstone's stake acquisition in Bagmane Group entities
news.para: US-based Blackstone is the world's largest alternative asset manager, with more than USD 1 trillion in assets under management (AUM).

news.title: Sunac China secures partial approval for onshore restructuring plan: Source
news.para: Two of the ten onshore bonds in the restructuring have received sufficient support from holders, the person said. The company will delay the voting deadline for the rest of the bonds to Dec. 23.

news.title: Bengaluru: Residents of Kithaganur and Halehalli panchayat demands basic amenities
news.para: VP Krishna, the Founder of the Federation, emphasised the urgency of these demands, stating, “Our daily lives are severely disrupted due to poor infrastructure and lack of basic amenities.

news.title: Karnataka: Quarry owners opposes one-time settlement scheme
news.para: The Cabinet’s decision is aimed at collecting the pending penalty amounting to Rs 6,105 crore from the miners in the state.

news.title: Agarwal Holdings acquires land parcel for Rs 455 crore in Mumbai’s Juhu
news.para: The transaction was finalized and registered in November 2024, with a stamp duty of Rs 27.30 crore and registration charges amounting to Rs 30,000.

news.title: Blackstone acquires LOGOS India’s 5 million sq ft warehousing assets for Rs 1,725 crore
news.para: The deal indicates Blackstone’s continued focus on strengthening its presence in India’s rapidly expanding logistics and supply chain infrastructure sector.
